President Trump announced in a press conference that the United States will be imposing tariffs on Chinese products, as well as other actions, in an effort to address the country's trade deficit with China. Trump stated that the US has a trade deficit of $504 billion with China, and he has asked China to reduce the trade deficit immediately by $100 billion. The President also mentioned that the US is renegotiating NAFTA and starting negotiations with the European Union. The actions against China include tariffs on certain products, investment restrictions, and filing a WTO case. The President emphasized the need for reciprocal trade, where both countries charge the same tariffs for products. The press conference included remarks from Ambassador Lighthizer and Secretary Ross, who outlined the issues with China's trade practices and the importance of protecting intellectual property rights. The President also mentioned that negotiations are ongoing and expressed optimism that deals will be reached.